      "text": "# The problem\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "824c9c93a3c605a6",
      "text": "The intuition was that it is a problem when politics looses its sincerity. When it is an accepted fact that all politicians are liars, and when increasingly politicians are drawn from a pool of people that are not simply good on television (Kennedy), but actual actors (Reagan), or reality television stars (Trump) - then we have a problem.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "f1c7ea296528a0ab",
      "text": "The problem is not just that we cannot trust what we are being told, but that a general sense of cynicism pervades all social and political decision making - without any countervailing idealism. This reduces our ability to take collective action in the face of complex system problems.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "500a4a2f198f6c14",
      "text": "# Double take\nBut what if it is not a problem. What if this is exactly what we need? That was the thought experiment that led to [[MCYP]] and eventually [[Liquid Democracy]]. Let's require politicians to be actors. Redefine their job description. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e2103f198e992b80",
      "text": "No longer will we think of them as leaders or decision makers - thats the job of the script writer and director. Lets' take the model of film and televisions and apply it directly to the structure of parliament.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "682f6e12133e8b15",
      "text": "# The solution\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "25351d8572409b2f",
      "text": "1. All politicians are presenters or actors\n1. No politician is allowed to make decisions\n1. No decision makers are allowed to appear on television (or similar real-time media).\n1. All decisions are to be made based on deliberations that have appropriate levels of transparency and public scrutiny.\n1. We call the platform for deliberation and decision making that our actors (politicians) use as scripts for their speeches - [[Liquid Democracy]].\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "13c6e0998724b219",
      "text": "# Discussion\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "de5af3edcf94aca2",
      "text": "It has taken a long, a very long time to develop the tools, techniques and technologies needed to create this platform. It has to be according to this definition a multimedia platform. Modern media after all is explicitly part of the problem and the solution. So we need a relatively sophisticated integration of media into the platform.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e2fa414d660bdc0c",
      "text": "We also need a sophisticated [[collaborative writing]] platform, and very little investment in such technologies has taken place leaving us with [[Wikipedia]], [[Stream based media]], and a range of failed alternatives. [[Federated Wiki]] is the closest we have got to approaching this ideal.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "3b692a3262b64511",
      "text": "Finally we also need robust [[self sovereign identity]], and the ability to make legally binding decisions over how money is invested, and how the collective (group, community, company, or country) commits to act. This was not been possible, or at least it was not an affordable option until the recent advances in legal precedent, blockchain and decentralised identity became freely available.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "7970136667306c62",
      "text": "We are still waiting for some of the final pieces, most important among them is [[self sovereign identity]]. When this is standardised, and in particular when this is built into our internet browsers by default - then we are getting somewhere.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "66ae7d115d4f2979",
      "text": "It has taken a long time for the communities required to come together, but there is now a critical mass of open (internet) standards people, software developers, lawyers, and business activity that has built up around the early ideas of activists and dreamers to make this a possibility in the real world. For me its been over 30 years now. I thought it would take less than 10."
